         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">20/1/89. ¶  ¶ Would you be so kind, esteemed Mr Tepper, as to give me information from the rich store of your experience as an entomologist, whether a small curious bee produces a honey there that is ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">89.01.20</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Otto Tepper</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M198, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Tepper: 'Reply 22.1.89 &amp; enclosed letter returned'. Letters not found.</p>
               </note>20/1/89.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Würden Sie so freundlich sein, geehrter Herr Tepper, mir aus dem reichen Schatz Ihrer Erfahrungen als Entomologe Auskunft zu geben, ob eine kleine eigenthümliche Biene dort einen Honig liefert, der von <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>-Prinzipien durchdrungen ist, und daher besondere medicinischen Werth haben würden. Ihr Name soll bei dieser Gelegenheit nicht genannt werden</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Sie ehrend der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">Erst eben erhole ich mich von den Extra-Arbeiten des Congresses. So habe ich die Bände der Leopoldina, welche Sie gütig sandte, kaum ansehen können.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Nimmt Honig aus Eucal. Regionen von gewöhnlichen Bienen den Geschmack u Geruch von Euc. an?</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">20/1/89.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would you be so kind, esteemed Mr Tepper, as to give me information from the rich store of your experience as an entomologist, whether a small curious bee produces a honey there that is full of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>
               </seg> principles and therefore would have particular medicinal value. Your name shall not be mentioned on this occasion.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Respectfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I am only just recovering from the extra work of the Congress,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Intercolonial Medical Congress of Australasia, Melbourne, January 1889.</p>
               </note> so I have scarcely been able look at the volumes of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Leopoldina</seg> that you kindly sent.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Tepper had sent M some volumes of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Leopoldina</seg> in response to M to O. Tepper, 28 November 1888.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Does honey of common bees from <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name> regions take on the taste and smell of <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>?</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>
            </p>
         </div>
